cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the optimization of mode selection and channel assignment in a cellular network with underlaying D2D communications. The paper focuses on managing interference and ensuring QoS requirements for both cellular and D2D links. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves simulations, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
